 root, drop a stun, and beat away.  Breaking mez, make sure you root first, cause it's going right to the enchanter to quickly beat the crap out of him, break with a stun <p><b>=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=<font face = "Arial"><br>Fenar Honorblade<br>Xegony<br></font>60th level Crusader of Mithanial Marr<br><i><b>Shards of Avalon<br></b>http://www.shardsofavalon.net<br></font>"Our own heart, and not other men's opinion, forms our true honor." <br>-Samuel Taylor Coleridge<br><i>Official President of the FoF: Friends of Fenar Corp.</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukellimloh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kellim LoH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/11/02 12:32:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunting in CT Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> Aside from breaking mez, there's no need to root. Simply chain stun/cease/desist. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udondorholystorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DondorHolystorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/11/02 3:28:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunting in CT Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> Root stops summoning <p>"Death smiles at us all, all a man can do is smile back."<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=84371" target="_blank">Dondor Holystorm</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=logansan>Logansan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.users.bigpond.net.au/romagames/images/loganson.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/11/02 3:47:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunting in CT Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> I found the best way to taunt in CT was simply to outdamage everyone except the rogues <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><B><FONT SIZE="4" COLOR="yellow"><A HREF="http://www.users.bigpond.net.au/romagames/eq.htm#Logansan">Logansan</A></B></FONT></BR><FONT COLOR="#66FFFF">59 Knight - Xev</FONT></BR><B><FONT COLOR="#FF9999">Founding Member of <A HREF="http://www.the-hand.net/">The Hand</A></FONT></B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaeriusshadowbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerius Shadowbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/11/02 10:41:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunting in CT Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> As said above, breaking mez is the only issue. But agro is quickly regained. I just use my normal combo taunt/disarm/cease/desist and occasional stun. Was fighting there the other night and never lost agro.<br><br>Aerius. <p><img src="http://www.warlocksdomain.com/.sig/aerius_small.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukellimloh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kellim LoH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 11:54:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunting in CT Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> Aye, root prevents summoning, but what I'm saying is that with judicious use of low mana stuns, you'll be on the top of the hate list.<br><br>I do prefer to have the mob rooted when breaking a mez, but that's because it seems to me that it takes between 4-6 stuns to bump you over a chanter who mezzed/tashed/slowed a mob.<br><br>Assuming a pull of two mobs (the vast majority of my time in CT has been in the sewers and more than a few pulls are two mobs), the time it takes to get one of them mezzed is more than enough time for me to have gained solid aggro.<br><br>Speaking of the sewers, I'd like to say that the diseased mosquito is the debbil. 30-40 hours down there and he's popped 3 times. One of those times he dropped a gimp wand that you wouldn't give to a twink, let alone see a level 51+ int caster use.<br><br>Good thing the EXP there is damn good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueqhalam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQHalam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 6:50:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunting in CT Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> Ive found the best taunt down there to be Healing Wave of Prexus.  Its a good save for the chanter since you can generally get 3 or 4 mobs to aggro on you as soon as it goes off, and it doesnt get interrupted much.<br><br>Halam<br>Erud Crusader of Luclin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upunkassgypsy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Punkass Gypsy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 11:52:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunting in CT Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> Taunt<br>Cease<br>Desist<br><br>Cast each one twice at the start, never lose aggro even with 2 epic monks and 2 epic rogues in group. <p><p><a href="http://pub31.ezboard.com/bradiance88931"><img border="0" src="http://www.users.qwest.net/~rndtable/TristSig6.jpg" width="507" height="154"></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirderekdrygon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Derek Drygon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 223<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/13/02 7:57:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://champions.morpheus.net/pics/derek2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunting in CT Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> I load up 3 stuns when hunting in CT and I use them, and them alone, to gain agro.  Generally the stuns I use are Cease, Stun, Desist.   Or Cease, Stun, Force (knockback is nice for positioning mobs)<br><br>HWOP does the trick in a huge pull, but its mana costly and I can never justify wasting all that mana for just taunting purposes.<br><br><br><br>Sir Derek Drygon<br>59th rank Knight of Truth<br>Champions of Norrath<br>The Rathe <p>"Hear it not Heaven thine ministers have done it!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saorn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.tripod.co.uk/redhotant/icons/iconoc09.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 272<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/13/02 9:34:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunting in CT Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> Cease and Stun are all that I normally use here.<br><br>I always stun the mezzed mobs twice before breaking a mez in CT.   Most other places I just taunt/stun/taunt break. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucaladel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caladel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 392<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/13/02 11:11:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taunting in CT Suggestions Please</span><hr size=1> Root is the quickest way to get an npc off someone else. If you are in an area where it matters, always root before breaking mez. If you are in a crap area just beat it up and stun it after you break mez, thats good enough and the chanter wont die. Not always necessary but root before breaking mez is a good instinct.<br><br>Taunting other then that, any of your stuns will do, or fol(make sure things are snared first)<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=132.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=132.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=12><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=132.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.threadControl?topicID=132.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topic